-- R13-T4: Quotation Mechanics — § as data, modification, diffing
-- Tests: § pass-through, § modification, § comparison, data-vs-execution

⊢ original
  yield §target

  ⊢= §target ← §(
    ⊢ greet
      given name
      yield message

      ∴ Say hello to «name» warmly.

      ⊨ message mentions «name»
  )

⊢ add-oracle
  given original→§target
  yield §enhanced, added-oracle

  ∴ Read «§target» as a cell definition (NOT its output).
    Add a new oracle to the greet cell:
      ⊨ message is 1-2 sentences
    Return the modified definition as «§enhanced».
    Describe what you added in «added-oracle».

  ⊨ §enhanced contains all oracles from «§target»
  ⊨ §enhanced contains the new oracle "message is 1-2 sentences"
  ⊨ §enhanced preserves the ∴ body exactly
  ⊨ added-oracle describes the new oracle

  ⊨? on failure:
    retry with "You must return a CELL DEFINITION (starting with ⊢), not execute it" max 2

⊢ add-handler
  given add-oracle→§enhanced
  yield §hardened, added-handler

  ∴ Read «§enhanced» as a cell definition.
    Add a ⊥ handler for the name input:
      given name ⊥? skip with message ≡ "Hello, stranger!"
    Return the modified definition.

  ⊨ §hardened contains the ⊥? handler for name
  ⊨ §hardened preserves all existing oracles
  ⊨ added-handler describes the new handler

  given add-oracle→§enhanced ⊥? error-value(⊥)

⊢ diff
  given original→§target
  given add-handler→§hardened
  yield changes[], change-count, preserves-interface

  ∴ Compare «§target» (original) with «§hardened» (modified).
    List every difference.
    Determine whether the interface (given/yield) changed.

  ⊢= change-count ← |changes|

  ⊨ change-count ≥ 2 (at least: new oracle + new ⊥ handler)
  ⊨ preserves-interface = true (given/yield unchanged)
  ⊨ changes does NOT include "∴ body changed"

  given add-handler→§hardened ⊥? skip with changes ≡ ["comparison impossible — modification failed"], change-count ≡ 0, preserves-interface ≡ false

⊢ verify-data-not-executed
  given original→§target
  given add-oracle→§enhanced
  yield is-data, evidence

  ∴ Confirm that «§target» and «§enhanced» were treated as DATA
    throughout this program, not executed.

    Evidence that they are data:
    - No cell was "run" with a name input
    - No message output was produced
    - The § values were READ and MODIFIED, not INVOKED

    If any cell mistakenly executed the § values (produced a greeting
    message), report that as a failure.

  ⊨ is-data = true
  ⊨ evidence explains why § values were treated as data

  given add-oracle→§enhanced ⊥? skip with is-data ≡ false, evidence ≡ "Cannot verify — § modification failed"
